title: Grateful Dead Live at Rich Stadium on 1989-07-04
description: Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Cold Rain & Snow, Walkin' Blues, Row Jimmy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Stagger Lee, Looks Like Rain, Deal Touch Of Gray, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> I Will Take You Home-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Better AUD Of the two AUD sources on the archive at this time this is the better of the two, imo.

I had fun at this show and was pleasantly surprised with its power. I thought Rich Stadium in 1986 was rather weak but never really had high expectations for the GD"s high profile/stadium shows for that matter. Nonetheless I remember leaving with a good feeling from this one.
bestest buffalo? was this the choice venue of the east or am i wrong? well just ask the brothers and N2O heads @ the 4-21-2009 show.  what a scene. [need some overhead photos posted].
Great Show Traveled the east tour and this was a highlight. Very high energetic show here.

5 stars is really pushing it Decent show by all means, really major screw-ups that I've noticed. But 5 stars is a serious stretch.

Jerry's voice is weary at this point, the tempo is down for a couple of tunes, and the whole set just feels like a mediocore late 80's show. 

Levels aren't anything to write home about either.

I'm giving it 3 because while it's solid, it pales in comparison to a number of shows around here.
what a way to open a show This one was a lot of fun for those who were there, especially the opening 3 songs.

home town delight! the show in foxborough 2 nights prior opend 1st set with 
playin->crazy fingers(wow!!hows that for a set opener) ...the playin was just up to the jam where they cut it off and went into crazy fingers
and i waited the entire show for them to pop back
into the reprise but alas it was not to be.
Did they forget about it??? I have no idea.
but you can imagine my delight when 2 days later in my home town of Buffalo when the better part of the way through the second set the come creeping out of ship of fools to finish it off with the playin reprise!!!! yeah!Now thats a band! I dont know who else noticed it at the time
or later for that matter!? When i met back up w/friend after the show who had been with me in foxborough (who know there Dead) they seem to think i was off my rocker. but off course the tapes later upheld my version of this unusual occurence. I dont know if this has happend before
or after but i knew it happend that night.
being there i thought fox borrough was the better of the 2 shows but the tapes seem to indicate otherwise.
Great sound After tweaking windows EQ got killer sound and the best bass I've heard come out of these computer speakers. Thanks.
awesome bothe my parents where at this show roughly 15 rows back front the stage wierd huh
Jerry's Voice Hey Now...HAAAAAA his voice was fine, ya all read into the hype....LISTEN TO THE MUSIC............and re evaluate...........Garcia later!

Spectacular. The recording isn't great, but this has become one of my favorite shows. It really sounds a lot better when jammed loud in a car. This is a great set-list. The space is abnormally good and blends nicely to a great "i will take you home." Decent touch, Jerry is great on terrapin. A nice when i paint my masterpiece and a great row jimmy. Brent is great through the whole show, very nice morning dew. Stagger Lee fits nice between masterpiece and LLR. Love Brent's vocals on Man smart, women smarter....I don't know guys, this is a great late 80's.
Great Show I was at this show just in front of the sounboard, it was a fantastic with a great sunny day for an outdoor show CSN opened the show it was a magical day spent with my friends !

Rich Stadium = Great Vibes This album was stellar! 

Such a majestic performance, really brings me back to hear this again!

1990 was Better Just my opionion - but I thought the following year at Rich Stadium (not the place to see the boys) was better. 

It certainly seemed like the '86 show was more than 3 years prior to this one at the time. I would guess much of that had to do with Jerry's improved health. Still - having played at Silver Stadium in Rochester in '87 and '88 - Rich Stadium seemed like an enormous concrete venue.
 
But what can you do? Smile smile smile

Perhaps they had video rigs up and decided to release this, I am not sure.

Nice suprise for a 1st set LLR. The playing is solid. Second set is good but not as good (again in my opin) as the boys would crank out the following July.
3 stars and by now most people have the dvd or the album as a fellow commentator noted below.

loved this tour... went to i think 10 shows on this tour...and being from albany new york...had to truck on up to buffalo...thank you for the upload...great times...oh shit...flash back...double thank you....::::::::)))))))....
this is the show If i couldA bin there I would of been there,  what a terrific sound and spirit , just no SHAKEDOWN STREET

Actually 10,000 Maniacs opened, not CSN. CSN opened the following year. It was a fairly good show. Deal & Watchtower had Jerry rocking' his heart out. Also the interplay between him and Brent during NFA was particularly good. I went in early to see 10,000 Maniacs. there were only about 100 people.

reviews are so subjective aren`t they? I am amused by the lower ratings of this show. The audio is quality. It is part of the archive collection for some reason. NFA from this show, was used as part of the latest GD movie 2012. Apparently the remaining members of the GD are satisfied with it. As well, Jerry and Brent looked so happy and played wonderfully on the NFA footage.

A great night. Yes, I was there too.  And I never was someone who did a tour at a time.  I just finished high school and was getting ready for college at Indiana University, but we drove from Chicago to Foxboro, where our car broke dowm before the 7/2/89 sho but by maybe the next morning (I think we actually sleep outside of the garage), easy fix, so on 7/3, we're thinking we have to get from Foxboro to Buffalo.  And to meet up with our friends.  Ended up, never saw our hometown friends again, except at home 2 days later.  I'm sure we all have some crazy stories like this re: Dead Shows.  I'd love to hear them.  Peace, -Nick
- Awesome!

So many memories I was at this show, I was 17,  Brent still brings me to tears.  CSN opened/ I was on field.  I remember some guy foaming at the mouth in front of us, but other than trip man, everything was awesome.  This and alipe valley this year were shows that were never matched again although we had alot of fun in the years that followed,  I miss it so,  :) ;) ;)  theres nothing left to do but

good mellow real yellow what can't be said bout this show that ain't already been said?  they had just finished the filming for the video for touch of grey like a coupla hours before, so they prolly were real tired, but it ain't show much inthis show because they are smokin hard.  i mean HARD.  talk about awesome.

Wave that flag, wave it wide and high Some shows just required a tremendous effort to get in the gate.
My Buddy and i took the V.W. camper up to Rich Stadium and did we get hassled.
We got pulled over for D.W.A.H 
(driving while a hippie) 
The State troopers wanted to search everything in the camper and I mean everything.
All these heads driving by us as every single thing I owned was up for government inspection.
The strangest part of the affair was they wanted the Steal Your Face sticker photo-copy in the window. Send it to the lab. Also decided to seize my dried fruit from the natural Food Store which trust me was not cheap. I almost lost my cool but good thing I didn't because they found my friends bowl, (not the cereal eating one) and we had to do some fast talking to get out of that one.
Oh yeah, some of my paperwork was not in order for the State of N.Y. so they made my friend drive which was bizarre and probably dangerous because he had no clue how to drive stick. He learned quick and we finally got to the show but trust me we were somewhat beaten down by that time.
I guess looking back we were blessed to not have to spend the 4th of July in jail.
The show? Do not remember much besides the TERRAPIN STATION and finally after a few years on tour being totally in the moment for the U.S. Blues encore.
GREAT SHOW Pretty sure it was 10,000 maniacs that opened this show, unless i'm mistaking it for 87. all in all a very good show. cold rain and snow and the wheel were standouts. I was very high. lol

Terrapin great show
I saw Buffalo (Rich) from 86 on this was the best show ........of those shows!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Morning Dew Really awesome Morning Dew. The whole show is awesome but the Morning Dew is the stand out.

Sweetness and honey. I'll be downloading this ASTONISHING audience recording! Thanks to the genius that put 'ears' on the microphones.
5 for fidelity and 5 for fire in the boys.
Rich Stadium 1992 I highly recomend Rich Stadium 1992 Summer.

Great great show! I was at this show and it was just a fantastic day. With me were my two brothers and my sister, and it was the last time we all got to do something like this together. The first set rocked, probably one of the best first sets I ever attended. Maybe it was because we were all together, or maybe it was it was an awesome day at an awesome show. My sister and one of my brothers are gone now to join Jerry and Brent and the gang. But, when I listen to this, I feel we are together again.

Jerry & Brent making it rain An awesome Jerry and Brent moment at 5:05 of Looks Like Rain.  Listening to this for the first time this morning on my way to work and it got me all choked up...really beautiful man.

Crazy Coincidence I drove from NH to Buffalo for this show. Two days later i was working at my retail job back in NH and some guy hands me a dollar bill with the setlist of this show written in pen on the dollar bill.
I would kill to be at this show! Or that's at least what Chris said about it 😄
Better Audio on Youtube The audio for this show is much better on Youtube, on the Dead's official YT channel. Truckin Up To Buffalo show
